<font color="#FF0000">MY PSTD</font><br>
<tt>Mon Mar 17 19:39:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
PSTD was a term that the first time I had heard it involved a water tower and a &quot;crazed Vietnam veteran&quot;.  As I grew older I realized that it just was a term to label all &quot;those Guys&quot; living in the woods, burying food in the hills and walking around wearing combat fatigues.<br>
About 20 years of sleeping only two hours at a time at night; finding myself emotionally isolated from those who I loved; dealing or not dealing with rage that I felt and generally eating myself up to about 450 lbs.; so I could be the meanest s.o.b. in the valley.  I finally had an significant emotional event occur that prompted me to seek help.  Then I found out what PSTD really meant!<br>
My Dad also served in WW II  and survived the Battle of the Bulge.  His return was on a troop ship with what was left of his friends.  They got the opportunity to share and cry and remember and honor those that did not return.<br>
On May 24, 1967 I was in a forward gun position when I got the word to pack up and boogie.  Oh yeah I had my shortimers stick but because I had done 2 tours back to back I was getting out 90 days early.  On May 27, 1967 I was walking the streets of Portland, Oregon.  No time to remember because no one cared.  No one wanted to hear.  No one wanted to even speak to me.  I don't know to this day if it was me or them.<br>
My Dad and I talked and he understood the combat part, but didn't understand the rage, the lack of sleep, or PSTD.<br>
That happens here. At least the understanding.<br>
PSTD is a personal thing with each of us.  Each of us deal with it differently.  Some of us don't recognize it and some of us have a strong enough support background that we need to look at it.  To those who still are looking for answers this is as good as a place as any to get them.  I have gotten more intelligent and caring responses here than any Vet Center or group that I ever worked in.  Thanks, to you all!  Tanker,Art,JJ,Doc Del,Doc Spatz,the FNG Chris,Wingman. You guys are the support team. Keep it up, keep posting!<br>
Apologies to those I missed.
